# shlack Project Rules

Read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for full architecture. This is a **Rust ratatui TUI** Slack client (`shlack`), not a web app.

## Module ownership

| Change type | Primary file |
|-------------|--------------|
| Domain types | `src/models.rs` |
| Message convert/apply | `src/messages.rs`, `src/events.rs` |
| UI drawing | `src/ui/` |
| Keybindings / compose input | `src/input.rs` |
| Event loop / startup | `src/main.rs` |
| Workspace / pane orchestration | `src/app.rs` |
| Slack API / Socket Mode | `src/slack/` |
| Slash commands | `src/commands.rs` |
| Message rendering (mrkdwn) | `src/formatting.rs` |
| Pane data structures | `src/widgets.rs` |
| Split layout tree | `src/split_view.rs` |
| Disk persistence | `src/persistence.rs` |
| Config / setup | `src/config.rs` |

## Coding conventions

- **Minimal diffs** — match existing style; no new abstractions for one-off use.
- **Redraw flag** — set `needs_redraw = true` after state changes; avoid redundant `terminal.draw` calls.
- **Monotonic time** — use `std::time::Instant` for durations/expiry (typing, status), not `SystemTime`.
- **Async** — Slack I/O is `tokio`; heavy work off the hot path; use existing `oneshot`/`mpsc` patterns for background loads.
- **Serde** — config and layout are JSON; add `#[serde(default)]` for new optional fields.
- **No secrets** — never hardcode or commit tokens; config lives in `config/` or `~/.config/shlack/`.

## Build & verify

```bash
cargo build --release
cargo test
```

Unit tests in `messages.rs`, `events.rs`, `formatting.rs`, `split_view.rs`, `persistence.rs`.

## Adding features

- **Toggle:** `AppSettings` field → Ctrl+key in `input.rs` → draw in `ui/` → persisted via `App.settings`.
- **Slash cmd:** `commands.rs` match arm + help text.
- **Realtime event:** `SlackUpdate` variant → `slack/socket.rs` → `events::apply_update()`.
